[38;2;255;255;255mâº[39m [1mRoot Cause Analysis[22m

  Based on my LLDB debugging session, I have identified the root cause of
  the crash:

  [1mCrash Location[22m: Line 26 in [38;2;177;185;249mdemo-buggy.c[39m, in the [38;2;177;185;249madd_score[39m function
  s->scores[s->num_scores] = score;  [32m// CRASH HERE![39m

  [1mRoot Cause[22m: The [38;2;177;185;249mscores[39m field in the Student structure is set to NULL
  (0x0000000000000000) in the [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student[39m function at line 19:
  s->scores = [34mNULL[39m;  [32m// This will cause a segfault when we try to write to [39m
  [32mit[39m

  [1mWhat Should Have Happened[22m: Line 18 shows that memory allocation for the
  scores array was commented out:
  [32m// s->scores = malloc(100 * sizeof(float));  // Allocate space for 100 [39m
  [32mscores[39m

  [1mDetails[22m:
  - The program attempts to write to [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[0][39m when adding the first
  score (95.5) for Alice
  - Since [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m is NULL, this results in a write to memory address 0x0,
   causing [38;2;177;185;249mEXC_BAD_ACCESS[39m
  - The Student pointer itself is valid (0x000000014c804180) and properly
  initialized except for the scores array

  [1mFix Required[22m: Uncomment line 18 in the [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student[39m function to
  properly allocate memory for the scores array before use.

  TASK_COMPLETE
